3	088132e5-f6bd-4124-a5ce-f1705be36e9a	{"scope": "Rental housing market in the Netherlands; municipal regulation of landlords (verhuurders)", "subject": "Gemeenten (municipalities) as the party granted new competences; verhuurders (landlords) as the regulated parties subject to licensing and conduct requirements.", "norm_type": "competence", "conditions": "Bill expected to be brought to public consultation in 2021 ('dit jaar'); licensing requirement (vergunningplicht) may be imposed by municipalities in specific cases of serious or repeated landlord misconduct; management takeover triggered if a landlord rents without a required licence; Wet Bibob may serve as a ground for licence refusal.", "promulgation": "Minister van Binnenlandse Zaken en Koninkrijksrelaties (K.H. Ollongren), portfolio Volkshuisvesting", "act_identifier": "Wetsvoorstel landelijke grondslag voorschriften goed verhuurderschap en verhuurdersvergunning (concept; not yet formally named)", "legal_modality": "can", "norm_identifier": "signal-verhuurdervergunning-gemeenten-2021"}	dit jaar [2021] in consultatie worden gebracht	{"Housing / real estate","Data protection / privacy","Labour market"}	Monitor the internet consultation on the wetsvoorstel goed verhuurderschap en verhuurdersvergunning expected in 2021, assess the impact of proposed licensing requirements and management-takeover provisions on clients active as landlords or property managers, and track the Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens advice on inter-municipal data exchange for any data-compliance obligations.	A bill is being prepared to create a national statutory basis for good landlordship requirements and a municipal landlord licensing system (verhuurdervergunning), expected to be put out for public consultation in 2021, giving municipalities the power to impose uniform conduct standards on landlords and — in cases of serious misconduct — to require a rental licence and take over property management.	proposed	statutory	8	general	\N	2026-05-17 18:50:22.117962+00	5196	1025	{"Labour market": "The letter explicitly follows up on a commitment made at the AO arbeidsmigranten (3 February 2021), and the good landlordship approach is partly aimed at protecting labour migrants who are particularly vulnerable to rogue landlord behaviour.", "Housing / real estate": "The bill directly regulates the rental housing market by introducing nationally uniform landlord conduct standards and a municipal licensing system for landlords, including the possibility of management takeover of non-compliant properties.", "Data protection / privacy": "The minister has requested advice from the Autoriteit Persoonsgegevens on the legal possibilities for municipalities to exchange data about rogue landlords across regional boundaries, raising data protection questions that must be resolved before the legislative framework is finalised."}	\N
4	9dac5c86-862b-4e00-962a-4e5168218a3e	{"scope": "Civic integration (inburgering) system in the Netherlands, with knock-on effects on the Vreemdelingenwet 2000 and the Rijkswet op het Nederlanderschap", "subject": "Inburgeringsplichtigen (civic integration obligees) and gemeenten (municipalities); also IND, COA, and DUO as parties in the civic integration chain", "norm_type": "conduct", "conditions": "Applies to all inburgeringsplichtigen (asylum status holders, family migrants, and others subject to the Wet inburgering); new system targeted for entry into force in 2020; extra funding announced from 2019 per coalition agreement; deviation from B1 standard only permitted after objective test confirms B1 is unattainable despite considerable effort", "promulgation": "Minister van Sociale Zaken en Werkgelegenheid (W. Koolmees), mede in samenwerking met de Staatssecretaris van Justitie en Veiligheid", "act_identifier": "Wet inburgering (nieuw); tevens Regeling inburgering (wijziging per 1 juli 2018); Vreemdelingenwet 2000; Rijkswet op het Nederlanderschap; Participatiewet", "legal_modality": "ought", "norm_identifier": "signal-inburgering-stelselherziening-2018"}	2020 (beoogde inwerkingtreding nieuwe Wet inburgering); wijziging Regeling inburgering per 1 juli 2018	{"Labour market","Housing / real estate","Consumer protection"}	Monitor the legislative progress of the new Wet inburgering (targeted 2020) and the interim Regeling inburgering amendment (1 July 2018), and advise municipal clients and course-provider clients on their forthcoming obligations regarding the brede intake, PIP, course procurement, ontzorging, and the B1 language standard, as well as the consequential amendments to the Vreemdelingenwet 2000 and Rijkswet op het Nederlanderschap.	The Minister of Social Affairs and Employment proposes a comprehensive overhaul of the Dutch civic integration (inburgering) system, including a new Wet inburgering targeted for 2020, raising the language requirement to B1, mandatory personal integration plans (PIP), municipal responsibility for purchasing integration courses, financial support management (ontzorging) for status holders, and faster/more frequent sanctions for non-compliance.	proposed	policy_intent	8	budget	\N	2026-05-17 18:54:56.557531+00	11512	1124	{"Labour market": "The central goal of the reformed system is to get newcomers into paid employment as quickly as possible, with the VIA programme and B1 language requirement explicitly designed to improve labour market participation of persons with non-western migration backgrounds and asylum status holders.", "Consumer protection": "Newcomers subject to the integration obligation are directly affected as the holders of rights and obligations under the new system, including the abolition of the loan system for integration courses and the introduction of personal integration plans with enforceable sanctions.", "Housing / real estate": "Municipalities are assigned a directing role from the moment status holders are housed, including a mandatory ontzorging arrangement covering rent and fixed costs, and a broad intake assessment linked to housing allocation."}	\N
5	f072ca19-05b9-4af1-a895-d5020876fe78	{"scope": "Dutch pension system (second and third pillar), AOW retirement age, early-exit arrangements, disability insurance for self-employed, and sustainable employability — covering all pension contracts, pension funds, employers, employees, and self-employed persons in the Netherlands.", "subject": "Pension funds (pensioenuitvoerders), employers (werkgevers), employees (werknemers), social partners (werkgevers- en werknemersorganisaties), self-employed persons (zelfstandigen), and third-pillar retirement savers; the Dutch legislature as setter of the AOW age.", "norm_type": "conduct", "conditions": "Subject to ratification by social partners' constituencies (achterbannen); legislation to be developed from autumn 2019 with target legal framework from 2022; AOW age frozen at 66 years and 4 months in 2020–2021; RVU exemption (~€19,000 gross per full year) operative from 2021 for five years; disability insurance obligation for self-employed subject to workable EMU-neutral proposal by early 2020 and cabinet bill by summer 2020; lifecycle investment requirement and uniform fiscal premium ceiling to apply to all pension contracts; lump-sum withdrawal option capped at 10% of accrued old-age pension value at retirement date.", "promulgation": "Minister van Sociale Zaken en Werkgelegenheid (W. Koolmees), mede namens het kabinet-Rutte III en sociale partners.", "act_identifier": "Pensioenwet; Wet verbeterde premieregeling; Algemene Ouderdomswet (AOW); fiscale kaders pensioen (tweede en derde pijler)", "legal_modality": "ought", "norm_identifier": "signal-pensioenakkoord-2019"}	Wettelijk kader gereed met ingang van 2022; kabinetsvoorstel arbeidsongeschiktheidsverzekering zelfstandigen voor de zomer van 2020; voortgangsbrief aan Kamer najaar 2019.	{"Labour market","Financial services","Tax / fiscal","Consumer protection"}	Monitor the legislative trajectory of the pension system renewal — including the Pensioenwet and Wet verbeterde premieregeling amendments targeting 2022 — and advise clients in pension administration, financial services, and HR/employment on transition plan obligations, the new fiscal premium ceiling, the RVU exemption conditions, the disability insurance obligation for self-employed persons, and the collective value transfer (invaren) rules as draft legislation becomes available from autumn 2019 onwards.	The Dutch cabinet and social partners have reached a framework agreement (principeakkoord) to fundamentally renew the pension system by abolishing the doorsneesystematiek and introducing age-independent premiums, slowing the rise of the AOW retirement age, introducing a statutory disability insurance obligation for self-employed persons, and adopting a package of early-exit and sustainable-employability measures, with legislation targeting entry into force from 2022.	committed	policy_intent	8	general	\N	2026-05-17 18:57:00.126128+00	17094	1384	{"Tax / fiscal": "The reform introduces a uniform fiscal premium ceiling for all pension contracts including the third pillar, a new lump-sum withdrawal option (bedrag ineens), an RVU levy exemption, expanded leave-saving limits (50 to 100 weeks), and a 15-year budgetary spreading of coverage measures totalling €8 billion.", "Labour market": "The agreement directly restructures retirement age policy (AOW), introduces early-exit arrangements (RVU exemption), mandates disability insurance for self-employed workers, and funds sustainable employability and lifelong learning programmes for all workers and employers.", "Financial services": "Pension funds and insurers must adapt all pension contracts to the new premium-based system with age-independent premiums, lifecycle investment requirements, collective value transfer (invaren), and revised spreading and coverage ratio rules.", "Consumer protection": "Pension participants and retirees gain new rights (lump-sum option, personalised pension overview, lifecycle protection) and are protected against disproportionate disadvantage during the transition from the doorsneesystematiek, including mandatory employer transition plans and a generational balance assessment before legislation is submitted."}	\N
